Title : Pigmented villonodular synovitis in a child.
Date : 1993
Publication_type : Journal Article
Abstract : The authors present a case of pigmented villonodular synovitis (PVNS) in an adolescent with monarticular involvement of the ankle and without congenital anomalies or sibling involvement. Its rarity in the ankle and in childhood is discussed; a review of the clinical, radiological, and pathological features of PVNS is presented.
